<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-412-070  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 412 070.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Microprocessors and Microsystems  March 1990 v14 n2 p107(12).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Using the TMC2301 image resampling sequencer. (the TRW LSIProducts device is used to process video images in real time)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Eldon, John; Wegner, Rich.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A pair of TRW LSI Products (El Segundo, CA) TMC2301 imageresampling sequencers are used to implement a 2D image and a RGBimage warper and applied to several filtering and resamplingapplications.andP;  The TMC2301 is a controller/address generator thatgenerates addresses for pixels read from a frame buffer andprocesses them according to desired algorithms.andP;  The combinationof the device with data source and target memories, coefficientlook-up table, and multiplier-accumulator with a host videoprocessing system enables the real-time processing of videoimages.andP;  The primary components of the TMC2301 are the X or Yaddress generator, U-direction address generator, walk counter andcentral controller.andP;  A number of algorithms for resampling andfiltering applications are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   TRW LSI Products Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    TRW.andO;Product:   TRW LSI Products TMC2301 (Integrated circuit) (usage).andO;Topic:     Video SystemsImage ProcessingIntegrated CircuitsSpecificationsApplicationsFilteringSampling.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   TMC2301 simplified block diagram. (chart)Calculations from a nearest neighbour algorithm. (table)Pixel map showing rotation and compression. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>